Genetic Algorithms, Theory. 

Genetic Algorithms: The paper analyzes the performance of a genetic algorithm and compares it to a hill-climbing algorithm. It also discusses the features of an idealized genetic algorithm that give it a speedup over the hill-climbing algorithm. 

Theory: The paper provides theoretical analysis of the performance of the algorithms and identifies the features that contribute to their speedup. It also discusses how these features can be incorporated into a real genetic algorithm.
